Commuters have been warned of delays after a person was hit by a train at Fladbury in Oxfordshire. Lines in both directions have now reopened, but there may still be delays. The line affected is that between Oxford and Worcester Shrub Hill. Travellers should prepare for up to 60-minute delays or cancellations whilst the service recovers.  A further update on the service will be provided at 3.30pm today.  More to follow... 